text.section:
The Division Director shall examine any plan submitted under subsection (a) of this section and shall determine if:
The successor savings and loan association, if it is an association chartered under the laws of this State, satisfies the requirements of Subtitle 2 of this title that relate to organization as a savings and loan association; or
The successor savings and loan association, if it is a savings and loan association not chartered under the laws of this State, satisfies the requirements of the laws of the jurisdiction in which it is organized that relate to the organization of savings and loan associations in that jurisdiction; and
The plan would be consistent with adequate and sound savings and loan practices and in the public interest. In making the determination required by this paragraph, the Division Director shall consider:
The financial history and condition of the parties to the plan;
Their prospects;
The management of the association;
The effect of the plan on competition; and
The convenience and needs of the area in this State primarily to be served by the resulting association.
